    "data": "بِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْم\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful\nعَن جَابِرِ ابْنِ عَبْدِ اللهِ الْاَنْصَارِىْ \nJabir bin Abdullah Ansari (r.a.) narrates \nعَنْ فَاطِمَةَ الزَّاهْرَاءِ عَلَيْهَا السَّلَامُ \nA’N FAATEMATAZ ZAHRAAE A’LAIHAS SALAAMO \nfrom Janab-e-Fatemah al-Zahra (a.s.).\nبِنْتِ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ اٰلِهٖ وَ سلَّمَ \nBINTE RASOOLIL LAAHE SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI WA SALLAMA \nthe daughter of the Messenger of Allah (s.a.w.a.) is to have thus related:\nقَالَ سَمِعْتُ فَاطِمَةَ اَنَّهَا قَالَتْ \nQAALA SAME'TO FAATEMATA ANNAHAA QAALAT\nHe (Jabir) said: I heard from Fatemah (s.a.) that she stated that\nدَخَلَ عَلَىَّ اَبِىْ رَسُوْلُ اللهِ فِىْ بَعْضِ الْاَيَّامِ \nDAKHALA A’LAIYYA ABI RASOOLUL LAAHE FEE BA’ZIL AYYAAME.\none day, my father the Messenger of Allah came to me, \nفَقَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكِ يَا فَاطِمَةُ \nFA QAALA ASSALAMO A’LAIKE YAA FATEMATO,\nand said, ‘Peace be upon you, O Fatemah (s.a.)!’\nفَقُلْتُ عَلَيْكَ السَّلَامُ \nFA-QULTO A’LAIKAS SALAAMO, \nSo I said: ‘Peace be upon you also.’\nقَالَ اِنِّىْٓ اَجِدُ فِىْ بَدَنِىْ ضُعْفًا \nQAALA INNEE AJEDO FEE BADANee ZO’FAN.\nHe said: ‘I am feeling weakness in my body.’\nفَقُلْتُ لَهٗ اُعِيْذُكَ بِاللهِ يَآ اَبَتَاهُ مِنَ الضُّعْفِ \nFA-QULTO LAHU OE’EZOKA BIL-LAAHE YAA ABATAAHO MENAZ ZO’FE.\nThen I said to him: ‘I seek refuge for you O father in Allah from weakness.’\nفَقَالَ يَا فَاطِمَةُ اِيْتِيْنِىْ بِالْكِسَآءِ الْيَمَانِىْ فَغَطِّيْنِى بِهٖ\nFA-QAALA YAA FATEMATO EETEENEE BILKESAAA-IL YAMAANEE FA-GHATTEENI BEHI.\nThus he said: ‘O Fatimah (a.s.) bring me Yemeni shawl and cover me with it.’\nفَاَتَيْتُهٗ بِهٖ وَصِرْتُ اَنْظُرُ اِلَيْهِ وَ اِذَا وَجْهُهٗ\nFA ATAYTOHU BEHI WA SIRTO ANZORO ELAYHE WA EZAA WAJH-HOHU\nSo I brought it and covered him with it. I looked at him his face \nيَتَلَالَؤُ كَاَنَّهُ الْبَدْرُ فِىْ لَيْلَةِ تَمَامِهٖ وَ كَمَالِهٖ. \nYATALA’LAO KA-ANNAHUL BADRO FEE LAYLATE TAMAAMEHI WA KAMAALEHI.\nwhich was glittering like a moon at the night of its fullness and perfection.\nفَمَا كَانَتْ اِلَّا سَاعَةً وَّ اِذَا بِوَلَدِىَ الْحَسَنِ قَدْ اَقْبَلَ \nFAMA KAANAT ILLAA SAA-A’TANW WA EZA BE WALADEYAL HASANE QAD AQBALA \nNo more than a while passed when my son Hasan (a.s.) came in, \nوَ قَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكِ يَآ اُمَّاهُ \nWA QAALA ASSALAAMO A'LAYKE YAA UMMAAHO.\nand said: ‘Peace be upon you, O mother!’\nفَقُلْتُ وَ عَلَيْكَ السَّلَامُ يَا قُرَّةَ عَيْنِىْ وَ ثَمَرَةَ فُؤَادِىْ \nFA-QULTO WA A'LAYKAS SALAAMO YA QURRATA A’YNI WA SAMARATA FOAADI \nI said: ‘Peace be upon you, too, O delight of my eye and fruit of my heart!’ \nفَقَالَ يَا اُمَّاهُ اِنِّىْٓ اَشُمُّ عِنْدَكِ رَآئِحَةً طَيِّبَةً \nFA-QAALA YAA UMMAAHO INNEE ASHUMMO I’NDAKE RAAA-EHATAN TAYYEBATAN \nHe (Hasan [a.s.]) said: ‘O mother! I can smell a pure fragrance from you\nكَاَنَّهَا رَآئِحَةُ جَدِّىْ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ \nKA-AN-NAHAA RAAA-EHATO JADDEE RASOOLIL LAAHE.\nas the fragrance of my grandfather the Messenger of Allah.’\nفَقُلْتُ نَعَمْ اِنَّ جَدَّكَ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ \nFAQULTO NA-A’M INNA JADDAKA TAHTAL KESAAAE.\nI said: ‘Yes, your grandfather is under the cloak.’\nفَاَقْبَلَ الْحَسَنُ  نَحْوَ الْكِسَآءِ \nFA-AQBALAL HASANO NAHWAL KESAAA-E\nHasan (a.s.) moved towards the cloak \nوَ قَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا جَدَّاهُ يَا رَسُوْلَ اللهِ \nWA QAALA ASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YA JADDAAHO YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE \nand said, ‘Peace be upon you, O grandfather, O Messenger of Allah.\nاَتَاْذَنُ لِىْ اَنْ اَدْخُلَ مَعَكَ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ \nATA’ZANO LEE A’N ADKHOLA MA-A’KA TAHTAL KESAAA-E.\nWill you allow me to be with you under the cloak?’\nفَقَالَ وَ عَلَيكَ السَّلَامُ يَا وَلَدِىْ \nFA QAALA “WA A’LAYKAS SALAAMO YAA WALADEE\nThen he (Holy Prophet [s.a.w.a.]) said: ‘Peace be upon you too, my son \nوَ يَا صَاحِبَ حَوْضِىْ قَدْ اَذِنْتُ لَكَ \nWA YAA SAAHEBA HAUZI QAD AZINTO LAKA.\nand O the owner of my Pond (Hauz-e-Kausar). I permit you.’\nفَدَخَلَ مَعَهٗ تَحَتَ الِكِسَآءِ. \nFA DAKHALA MA-A’HU TAHTAL KESAAA-E.\nSo he (Hasan [a.s.]) entered under the cloak with him.\nفَمَا كَانَتْ اِلَّا سَاعَةً وَّ اِذَا بِوَلَدِىَ الْحُسَيْنِ  قَدْ اَقْبَلَ \nFAMAA KAANAT ILLAA SAA-A’TAWN WA EZAA BE WALADEYAL HUSAYNE QAD AQBALA \nNo more than a while passed when my son Husain (a.s.) came\nوَ قَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكِ يَآ اُمَّاهُ \nWA QAALA: “ASSALAAMO A’LAYKE YAA UMMAAHO”.\nand said: ‘Peace be upon you, O mother!’\nفَقُلْتُ وَ عَلَيْكَ السَّلَامُ يَا وَلَدِىْ \nFA-QULTO: “WA A'LAYKAS SALAAMO YAA WALADEE \nI said: ‘Peace be upon you also O my son\nوَ يَا قُرَّةَ عَيْنِىْ وَ ثَمَرةَ فُؤَادِىْ \nWA YAA QURRATA A’YNI WA SAMARATA FOAADEE”.\nO delight of my eye and fruit of my heart!’\nفَقَالَ لِىْ يَآ اُمَّاهُ اِنِّىْٓ اَشُمُّ عِنْدَكِ رَآئِحَةً طَيِّبَةً \nFA-QAALA LEE “YAA UMMAAHO INNEE ASHUMMO I’NDAKE RAA-EHATAN TAYYEBATAN \nHe said: ‘O mother! I can smell a pure fragrance from you\nكَاَنَّهَا رَآئِحَةُ جَدِّىْ رسُوْلِ اللهِ  \nKA-ANNAHAA RAAEHATO JADDEE RASOOLIL LAAHE”.\nas the fragrance of my grandfather the Messenger of Allah.’\nفَقُلْتُ نَعَمْ اِنَّ جَدَّكَ وَ اَخَاكَ تَحْتَ الْكِسَاءِ \nFA-QULTO: NA-A’M INNA JADDAKA WA AKHAAKA TAHTAL KESAAA-E”.\nSo I said: ‘Yes, your grandfather and your brother are under the cloak.’\nفَدَنَى الْحُسَيْنُ نَحْوَ الْكِسَاءِ \nFADANAL HUSAYNO NAHWAL KESAAA-E \nHusain (a.s.) went towards the cloak \nوَ قَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا جَدَّاهُ \nWA QAALA “ASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YAA JADDAAHO \nand he said, ‘Peace be upon you, O grandfather, \nاَلسَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا مَنِ اخْتَارَهُ اللهُ \nASSALAAMO ALAYKA YAA MANIKHTAARAHUL LAAHO \nPeace be upon you, O chosen of Allah\nاَتَاْذَنُ لِىْٓ اَنْ اَكُوْنَ مَعْكُمَا تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ؟ \nATAAZANO-LEE A’N ADKHOLA MA-A’KOMA TAHTAL KESAAE?\nWill you allow me to be with both of you under the cloak?’\nفَقَالَ عَلَيْكَ السَّلَامُ يَا وَلَدِىْ \nFA QAALA A'LAYKAS SALAAMO YAA WALADEE\nHe said, ‘Peace be upon you too, O my son \nوَ يَا شَافِعَ اُمَّتِىْ قَدْ اَذِنْتُ لَكَ \nWA YAA SHAAFEA UMMATEE QAD AZINTO LAKA\nAnd O the interceder of my ummah. Surely I allow you.’\nفَدَخَلَ مَعَهُمَا تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ. \nFA-DAKHALA MA-A’HOMA TAHTAL KESAAAE.\nso he (Husain [a.s.]) entered with both of them under the cloak.\nفَاَقْبَلَ عِنْدَ ذٰلِكَ اَبُو الْـحَسَنِ \nFA-AQBALA I’NDA ZAALEKA ABUL HASANE \nJust then Abul Hasan (Ali [a.s.]) came,\nعَلِىُّ بْنُ اَبِيْ طَالِبٍ وَ قَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكِ \nA’LIYYUBNO ABEE TAALEBIN WA QAALA: “ASSALAAMO A’LAYKE \nAli ibn Abi Talib (a.s.) said: ‘Peace be upon you, \nيَا بِنْتَ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ \nYAA BINTE RASOOLIL LAAHE”.\nO daughter of the Messenger of Allah’.\nفَقُلْتُ وَ عَلَيْكَ السَّلَامُ يَآ اَبَا الْحَسَنِ \nFA-QULTO “WA A’LAYKAS SALAAMO YAA ABAL HASANE \nI replied: ‘Peace be upon you also, O Abul Hasan \nوَ يَآ اَمِيْرَ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ \nWA YAA AMEERAL MOMENEEN”.\nand O Commander of the Faithful.’\nفَقَالَ يَا فَاطِمَةُ اِنِّىْ اَشُمُّ عِنْدَكِ رَآئِحَةً طَيِّبَةً \nFA-QAALA “YAA FAATEMATO, INNI ASHUMMO I’NDAKE RAAEHATAN TAYYEBATAN \nHe then said, ‘O Fatemah (s.a.)! I can smell a pure fragrance from you \nكَاَنَّهَا رَائِـحَةُ اَخِىْ وَ ابْنِ عَمِّىْ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ \nKA ANNAHAA RAAEHATO AKHEE WABNE AMMI RASOOLIL LAAHE”.\nlike that of my brother and cousin the Messenger of Allah.’\nفَقُلْتُ نَعَمْ هَا هُوَ مَعَ وَلَدَيْكَ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ \nFA-QULTO “NA-A’M HAA HOWA MA-A’ WALADAYKA TAHTAL KESAAA-E”, \nI said, ‘Yes, he is under the cloak with your two sons.’\nفَاَقْبَلَ عَلِىٌّ نَحْوَ الْكِسَآءِ \nFA-AQBALA A’LIYYUN NAHWAL KESAAE, \nSo Ali (a.s.) went towards the cloak \nوَ قَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا رَسُوْلَ اللهِ \nWA QAALA “ASSALAAMO ALAYKA YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE, \nand said, ‘Peace be upon you, O Messenger of Allah! \nاَتَاْذَنُ لِىْ اَنْ اَكُوْنَ مَعَكُمْ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ؟\nATA’ZANO LEE A’N AKOONA MA-A’KUM TAHTAL KESAAA-E?”\nMay I be with you (all) under the cloak?’\nقَالَ لَهٗ وَ عَلَيْكَ السَّلَامُ يَآ اَخِىْ يَآ وَصِيِّىْ \nQAALA LAHU “WA ALAYKAS SALAAMO YAA AKHEE, WA YAA WASIYYEE \nHe (Holy Prophet [s.a.w.a.]) replied, ‘Peace be upon you too, O my brother, my legatee, \nوَ خَلِيْفَتِىْ وَ صَاحِبَ لِوَآئِىْ قَدْ اَذِنْتُ لَكَ \nWA KHALIFATEE WA SAAHEBA LEWAAA-EE QAD AZINTO LAKA” \nmy successor and my standard bearer, you are permitted.’\nفَدَخَلَ عَلِىٌّ تَحَتَ الْكِسَآءِ. \nFA-DAKHALA A’LIYYUN TAHTAL KESAAA-E. \nSo Ali (a.s.) entered the cloak.\nثُمَّ اَتَيْتُ نَحْوَ الْكِسَآءِ \nSUMMA ATAYTO NAHWAL KESAAA-E \nThen I (Fatemah [s.a.]) came towards the cloak \nوَ قُلْتُ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ يَآ اَبَتَاهُ يَا رَسُوْلَ اللهِ \nWA QULTO “ASSALAAMO A’LAYKA YAA ABATAAHO, YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE \nand said, ‘Peace be upon you O father, O Messenger of Allah. \nاَتَأْذَنُ لِىْ اَنْ اَكُوْنَ مَعَكُمْ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ؟\nATA’ ZANO LEE A’N AKOONA MA-A’KUM TAHTAL KESAAA-E?”\nAm I allowed to be with you under the cloak?’\nوَ قَالَ وَ عَلَيْكِ السَّلَامُ يَا بِنْتِىْ \nWA QAALA “WA A’LAYKIS SALAAMO YAA BINTEE \nHe replied, ‘Peace be upon you also, O my daughter \nوَ يَا بِضْعَتِىْ قَدْ اَذِنْتُ لَكِ \nWA YAA BAZ-A’TEE QAD AZINTO LAKE”\nand O my part, you are allowed.’\nفَدَخْلتُ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ. \nFA-DAKHALTO TAHTAL KESAAA-E.\nSo I entered the cloak.\nفَلَمَّا اكْتَمَلْنَا جَمِيْعًا تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ \nFA-LAMMAK TAMALNAA JAMEE-A’N TAHTAL KESAAA-E \nWhen we (Panjatan Paak) all gathered under the cloak, \nاَخَذَ اَبِىْ رَسُوْلُ اللهِ بِطَرَفَىِ الْكِسَآءِ \nAKHAZA ABEE RASOOLIL LAAHE BE TARAFAYIL KESAAA-E, \nmy father, the Messenger of Allah, held the two ends of the cloak \nوَ اَوْمَئَ بِيَدِهِ الْيُمْنٰى اِلَى السَّمَآءِ وَ قَالَ \nWA AWMA-A BE-YADEHIL YUMNA ELAS SAMAAE WA QAALA: \nand raised his right hand towards the heavens and said:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اِنَّ هٰؤُلَآءِ اَهْلُ بَيْتِىْ \nALLAAHUMMA INNA HAAAOOLAAE AHLO BAYTEE, \nO Allah, these are the people of my household (Ahle Bayt). \nوَ خَاصَّتِىْ وَ حَآمَّتِىْ \nWA KHAASSATEE, WA HAAMMATEE \nand my confidants and my supporters.\nلَحْمُهُمْ لَحْمِىْ وَ دَمُهُمْ دَمِىْ \nLAHMOHUM LAHMI, WA DAMOHUM DAMEE\nTheir flesh is my flesh and their blood is my blood.\nيُؤْلِمُنِىْ مَا يُؤْلِمُهُمْ وَ يَحْزُنُنِىْ مَا يَحْزُنُهُمْ \nYO’LEMONI MAA YO’LEMOHUM WA YAHZONONI MAA YAHZONOHUM, \nWhoever hurts them hurts me, whoever grieves them grieves me.\nاَنَا حَرْبٌ لِّمَنْ حَارَبَهُمْ \nANAA HARBUN LEMAN HAARABAHUM \nI am at war with those who wages war with them.\nوَ سِلْمٌ لِّمَنْ سَالَمَهُمْ \nWA SILMUN LEMAN SAALAMAHUM, \nI am at peace with those at peace with them.\nوَ عَدُوٌّ لِّمَنْ عَادَاهُمْ وَ مُحِبٌّ لِّمَنْ اَحَبَّهُمْ \nWA ADUWWUN LEMAN A’ADAAHUM WA MOHIBBUN LEMAN AHABBAHUM \nI am the enemy of their enemies and I am the friend of their friends.\nاِنَّهُمْ مِنِّىْ وَ اَنَا مِنْهُمْ \nINNAHUM MINNI WA ANA MINHUM \nThey are from me and I am from them.\nفَاجْعَلْ صَلَوٰتِكَ وَ بَرَكَاتِكَ وَ رَحْمَتَكَ \nFAJ-A’L SALAWAATAKA WA BARAKAATAKA WA RAHMATAKA \n(O Allah!) Bestow Your Blessings, your Favour, and Your Grace \nوَ غُفْرَانَكَ وَ رِضْوَانَكَ عَلَىَّ وَ عَلَيْهِمْ \nWA GHUFRAANAKA WA RIZWANAKA A’LAYYA WA A’LAYHIM \nand Your Forgiveness and Your willingness upon me and upon them. \nوَ اَذْهِبْ عَنْهُمُ الرِّجْسَ وَ طَهِّرْهُمْ تَطْهِيْرًا. \nWA AZHIB ANHOMUR RIJSA WA TAHHIRHUM TATHEERAA.\nAnd remove impurity from them and keep them thoroughly pure.” (Salawaat)\nفَقَالَ اللهُ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ يَا مَلَآئِكَتِىْ \nFA-QAALAL LAAHO A'ZZA WA JALLA YAA MALAAA-EKATEE \nThen Allah – Mighty and Glorified be He – said: ‘O my angels! \nوَ يَاسُكَّانَ سَمٰوٰتِىْ \nWA YAA SUKKAANA SAMAAWAATEE \nand O the residents of my heavens, \nاِنِّىْ مَا خَلَقْتُ سَمَآءً مَّبْنِيَّةً وَّ لَا اَرْضًا مَّدْحِيَّةً\nINNEE MAA KHALAQTO SAMAAA-A’M MABNIYYATAN WA LAA ARZAN MADHIYYATAN \nI have not created the high heaven and stretched earth, \nوَّ لَا قَمَرًا مُّنِيْرًا وَّ لَا شَمْسًا مُّضِيٓئَةً \nWA LAA QAMARAM MONEERAN WA LAA SHAMSAN MOZEE-A’TAN, \nand illuminating moon and shinning sun \nوَّ لَا فَلَكًا يَّدُوْرُ وَ لَا بَحْرًا يَّجْرِىْ \nWA LAA FALAKAN YADOORO WA LAA BAHRAYN YAJREE\nand the rotating planets and the flowing rivers\nوَ لَا فُلْكًا يَّسْرِىْٓ اِلَّا فِىْ مَحَبَّةِ هٰؤُلَآءِ الْخَمْسَةِ \nWA LAA FULKAN YASREE, ILLAA FEE MAHABBATE HAA-OOLAAA-IL KHAMSATIL \nand the sailing ships, but for the love of these five \nالَّذِيْنَ هُمْ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ \nLAZEENA HUM TAHTAL KESAAA-E.\nwho are under the cloak.’\nفَقَالَ الْاَمِيْنُ جَبْرَآئِيْلُ يَا رَبِّ \nFA QAALAL AMEENO JABRAEELO YAA RABBE \nThen Gabriel, the trusted angel, asked, ‘O my Lord! \nوَ مَنْ تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ؟ \nWA MAN TAHTAL KESAAA-E?\nWho are those under the cloak?’\nفَقَالَ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ هُمْ اَهْلُ بَيْتِ النُّبُوَّةِ \nFA-QAALA A'ZZA WA JALLA HUM AHLO BAYTIN NOBUWWATE \nThe Mighty and Glorified answered, ‘They are the household of Prophethood \nوَ مَعْدِنُ الرِّسَالَةِ \nWA MA’DENUR RESAALATE \nand the mines of apostleship.\nهُمْ فَاطِمَةُ وَ اَبُوْهَا وَ بَعْلُهَا وَ بَنُوْهَا. \nHUM FAATEMATO WA ABOOHA WA BA’LOHAA WA BANOOHAA. \nThey are: Fatemah and her father and her spouse and her sons.’ (Salawaat)\nفَقَالَ جَبْرَآئِيْلُ يَا رَبِّ اَتَأْذَنُ لِىْٓ \nFA QAALA JABRAAA-EELO YAA RABBE ATA’ZANO LEE \nGabriel asked, ‘O my Lord! Do you permit me\nاَنْ اَهْبِطَ اِلَىْ الْاَرْضِ لِاَكُوْنَ مَعَهُمْ سَادِسًا؟ \nA’N AHBETA ELAL ARZE LE-AKOONA MA-A’HUM SAADESAA. \nto descend to the earth that I be the sixth with them?’\nفَقَالَ اللهُ نَعَمْ قَدْ اَذِنْتُ لَكَ \nFA QAALAL LAAHO NA-A’M QAD AZINTO LAKA.\nAllah said, ‘Yes, you are permitted.’\nفَهَبَطَ الْاَمِيْنُ جَبْرَآئِيْلُ \nFAHABATAL AMEENO JABRAAA-EELO \nSo Gabriel the trusted Archangel descended, \nوَ قَالَ السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكَ يَا رَسُوْلَ اللهِ \nWA QAALAS SALAAMO A’LAYKA YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE\nAnd said, ‘Peace be upon you, O Messenger of Allah!’\nاَلْعَلِىُّ الْاَعْلٰى يُقْرِئُكَ السَّلَامُ \nAL-A’LIYYUL A’ALAA YUQRE-OKAS SALAAMO \n‘The All-Highest (Allah) conveys to you His greeting, \nوَ يَخُصُّكَ بِالتَّحِيَّةِ وَالْاِكْرَامِ \nWA YAKHUS-SOKA BITTAHIYYATE WAL IKRAAME \nand expresses His special greeting and respect to you, \nوَ يَقُوْلُ لَكَ وَ عِزَّتِىْ وَ جَلَآلِىْ \nWA YAQOOLO LAKA WA I’ZZATEE WA JALAALI \nand says, ‘By my Honour and my Dignity\nاِنِّىْ مَا خَلَقْتُ سَمَآءً مَّبْنِيَّةً \nINNEE MAA KHALAQTO SAMAA-AN MABNIYYATAN \nI have not created high heaven\nوَّ لَا اَرْضًا مَّدْحِيَّةً وَّ لَا قَمَرًا مُّنِيْرًا \nWA LAA ARZAN MADHIYYATAN WA LAA QAMARAN MONEERAN \nand the stretched earth and the illuminated moon, \nوَّ لَا شَمْسًا مُّضِٓيْئَةً وَّ لَا فَلَكًا يَّدُوْرُ \nWA LAA SHAMSAM MOZEE-ATANW WA LAA FALAKAN YADOORO \nand the bright sun, and the rotating planet, \nوَ لَا بَحْرًا يَّجْرِىْ وَ لَا فُلْكًا يَّسْرِىْ \nWA LAA BAHRAN YAJRI WA LAA FULKAN YASREE\nand flowing ocean, and the sailing ships, \nاِلَّا لِاَجْلِكُمْ وَ مَحَبَّتِكُمْ \nILLAA LE-AJLEKUM WA MAHABBATEKUM \nbut for your sake and your love.’\nوَ قَدْ اَذِنَ لِىْ اَنْ اَدْخُلَ مَعَكُمْ \nWA QAD AZENA LEE A’N ADKHOLA MA-A’KUM \nAnd indeed He (Allah) has given me permission to enter the cloak with you.\nفَهَلْ تَاْذَنُ لِىْ يَا رَسُوْلَ اللهِ \nFA-HAL TA’ZANO LEE YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE. \nSo, O Messenger of Allah! Do you permit me? \nفَقَالَ رَسُوْلُ اللهِ وَعَلَيْكَ السَّلَامُ \nFA QAALA RASOOLAL LAAHE WA ALAYKAS SALAAMO \nThe Messenger of Allah replied: ‘And peace be on you also,\nيَآ اَمِيْنَ وَحْىِ اللهِ اِنَّهٗ نَعَمْ قَدْ اَذِنْتُ لَكَ \nYAA AMEENA WAHYIL LAAHE INNAHU NA-A’M QAD AZINTO LAKA, \nO trustee of Allah’s revelation! I permit you.’\nفَدَخَلَ جَبْرَآئِيْلُ مَعَنَا تَحَتَ الْكِسَآءِ \nFA-DAKHALA JABRAAA-EELO MA-A’NA TAHTAL KESAAA-E.\nSo, Gabriel entered the cloak with us. \nفَقَالَ لِاَبِىْ اِنَّ اللهَ قَدْ اَوْحىٰٓ اِلَيْكُمْ \nFA-QAALA LE-ABI INNAL LAAHA QAD AWHAA ELAYKUM \nThen said to my father, ‘Certainly Allah has revealed for you \nيَقُوْلُ ’اِنَّمَا يُرِيْدُ اللهُ لِيُذْهِبَ عَنْكُمُ الرِّجْسَ اَهْلَ الْبَيْتِ وَ يُطَهِّرَكُمْ تَطْهِيْراً‘ \nYAQOOLO, “INNAMAA YOREEDUL LAAHO LE-YUZHEBA A’NKOMUR RIJSA AHLAL BAYTE WA YOTAHHERAKUM TATHEERAA.” \nsaying, ‘Allah only desires to keep away the uncleanness from you, O people of the House, and to purify you a thorough purifying.’” (Salawaat)\nفَقَالَ عَلِىٌّ لِاَبِىْ يَا رَسُوْلَ اللهِ \nFA QAALA A’LIYYUN LE-ABEE YAA RASOOLAL LAAHE \nThen Ali (a.s.) said to my father, ‘O Messenger of Allah! \nاَخْبِرْنِى مَا لِـجُلُوْسِنَا هٰذَا تَحْتَ الْكِسَآءِ مِنَ الْفَضْلِ عِنْدَ اللهِ \nAKHBIRNI MAA LEJOLOOSENA HAAZA TAHTAL KESAAA-E MENAL FAZLE I’NDAL LAAHE.\nInform me what merits has Allah given for our getting together underneath this cloak?’\nفَقَالَ النَّبِىُّ وَ الَّذِىْ بَعَثَنِىْ بِالْحَقِّ نَبِيًّا \nFA QAALAN NABIYYO WAL-LAZEE BA-A’SANI BIL HAQQE NABBIYYAN \nThen the Prophet (s.a.w.a.) replied: ‘By Him Who rightfully sent me a Prophet\nوَّاصْطَفَانِىْ بِالرِّسَالَةِ نَجِيًّا مَّا ذُكِرَ خَبَرُنَا هٰذَا \nWASTAFAANI BIR RESAALATE NAJIYYAN MAA ZOKERA KHABARONA HAAZA \nand chose me for apostleship for the salvation (of mankind), whenever the event of this gathering of us \nفِىْ مَحْفِلٍ مِّنْ مَحَافِلِ اَهْلِ الْاَرْضِ \nFEE MAHFELIM MIN MAHAAFELE AHLIL ARZE, \nis mentioned in an assembly of the people of the earth \nوَ فِيْهِ جَمْعٌ مِّنْ شِيْعَتِنَا وَ مُحِبِّيْنَا \nWA FEEHE JAM-U’M MIN SHEEA’TENAA WA MOHIBBEENA \nin which a group of our followers and lovers are present, \nاِلَّا وَ نَزَلَتْ عَلَيْهِمُ الرَّحْمَةُ \nILLAA WA NAZALAT A’LAYHEMUR RAHMATO \nthe (divine) mercy shall be poured down on them \nوَحَفَّتْ بِهِمُ الْمَلَآئِكَةُ \nWA HAFFAT BEHEMUL MALAAA-EKATO \nand the angels shall encircle them, \nوَاسْتَغْفَرَتْ لَهُمْ اِلٰى اَنْ يَّتَفَرَّقُوْا \nWAS-TAGHFARAT LAHUM ELAA AYN YATAFARRAQOO.\nasking forgiveness for them until they depart.’ (Salawaat)\nفَقَالَ عَلِىٌّ اِذًا وَّ اللهِ فُزْنَا وَ فَازَ شِيْعَتُنَا وَ رَبِّ الْكَعْبَةِ\nFA QAALA A’LIYYUN A’LAYHIS SALAAMO EZAN WAL LAAHE FUZNAA WA FAAZA SHEEA’TONA WA RABBIL KAA’BATE. \nThen Ali (a.s.) said: ‘Verily, by Allah; we and our followers have succeeded by the Lord of Kabah.’\nفَقَالَ النَّبِىُّ ثَانِيًا يَا عَلِىُّ \nFA QAALAN NABIYYO SAANEYAN YAA A’LIYYO \nThen the Messenger of Allah (s.a.w.a.) said for the second time: ‘O Ali!\nوَ الَّذِىْ بَعَثَنِىْ بِالْحَقِّ نَبِيًّا \nWAL LAZEE BA-A’SANI BIL HAQQE NABIYYAN \nI swear by Him Who rightfully sent me as a Prophet\nوَّاصْطَفَانِىْ بِالرِّسَالَةِ نَجِيًّا مَّا ذُكِرَ خَبَرُنَا هٰذَا \nWAS TAFAANEE BIR-RESAALATE NAJIYYAN MAA ZOKERA KHABARONA HAAZA \nAnd chose me a Messenger for the salvation of the mankind, whenever the event of this gathering of us is mentioned \nفِىْ مَحْفِلٍ مِّنْ مَحَافِلِ اَهْلِ الْاَرْضِ \nFEE MAHFELIM MIN MAHAAFELE AHLIL ARZE \nin an assembly of the people of the earth \nوَ فِيْهِ جَمْعٌ مِّنْ شِيْعَتِنَا وَ مُحِبِّيْنَا \nWA FEEHE JAM-U’M MIN SHEEA’TENA WA MOHIBBEENA \nin which a group of our followers and lovers are present \nوَ فِيْهِمْ مَهْمُوْمٌ اِلَّا وَ فَرَّجَ اللهُ هَمَّهٗ \nWA FEEHIM MAHMOOMUN ILLAA WA FAR-RAJAL LAAHO HAMMAHU \nthere shall remain none grieved but Allah will remove his grief \nوَ لَا مَغْمُوْمٌ اِلَّا وَ كَشَفَ اللهُ غَمَّهٗ \nWA LAA MAGHMOOMUN ILLAA WA KASHAFAL LAAHO GHAMMAHU \nthere shall remain none distressed but Allah will dispel his distress \nوَ لَا طَالِبُ حَاجَةٍ اِلَّا وَ قَضَى اللهُ حَاجَتَهٗ \nWA LAA TAALEBO HAAJATIN ILLAA WA QAZAL LAAHO HAAJATAHU.\nthere shall remain none wish-seeker but Allah will grant his wish. (Salawaat)\nفَقَالَ عَلِيٌّ اِذًا وَّ اللهِ فُزْنَا وَ سُعِدْنَا \nFA-QAALA A’LIYYUN EZAN WAL LAAHE FUZNA WA SOI’DNAA \nThen Ali (a.s.) said: ‘Verily, by Allah; we \nوَ كَذٰلِكَ شِيْعَتُنَا فَازُوْا وَ سُعِدُوْا فِى الدُّنْيَا \nWA KAZAALEKA SHEEA’TONAA FAAZU WA SOE’DOO FID DUNYAA \nand our followers have achieved success and felicity in the world \nوَ الْاٰخِرَةِ وَ رَبِّ الْكَعْبَةِ.\nWAL AAKHERAH WA RABBIL KA’BATE.\nand the hereafter by the Lord of the Kabah. (Salawaat)", 
    "title": "Hadeese Kisa"
}